 -- Function: mod_load (PATH)
     Parse a ‘.mo’ file.  Returns a _model struct_ -- a list of ‘[tag =
     value]’ equations with these fields:

        • ‘name’ -- the model's name (string)
        • ‘params’ -- ‘[[symbol, default_value], ...]’
        • ‘states’ -- list of state-variable symbols (those with
          ‘der(...)’ in equations)
        • ‘derivs’ -- list of derivative symbols, one per state, named
          ‘der_<state>’
        • ‘inputs’ -- list of input-variable symbols
        • ‘outputs’ -- list of output-variable symbols
        • ‘initial’ -- ‘[[state, initial_value], ...]’ from ‘start =
          ...’ annotations
        • ‘residuals’ -- list of equations in residual form (each ≡ 0)

     Use ‘mod_get(m, 'states)’ to fetch a field.


