 -- Function: mod_dataflow (M, OP_POINT, [OPTS])
     Render the linearised state-space connectivity as a dataflow
     diagram.  Nonzero entries of ‘A’, ‘B’, ‘C’, ‘D’ become labelled
     edges:

     B[i,j] ≠ 0   →   input[j]  ──>  state[i]   (label: B[i,j])
     A[i,j] ≠ 0   →   state[j]  ──>  state[i]   (label: A[i,j])
     C[k,i] ≠ 0   →   state[i]  ──>  output[k]  (label: C[k,i])
     D[k,j] ≠ 0   →   input[j]  ──>  output[k]  (label: D[k,j])

     ‘opts’ is an optional list of equations:

        • ‘format’ -- ‘'dot’ (GraphViz, default), ‘'mermaid’, or
          ‘'edges’ (raw list).
        • ‘threshold’ -- hide edges with ‘|weight| < threshold’ (default
          ‘1e-12’).
        • ‘params’ -- parameter override list, passed to
          ‘mod_state_space’.

     Returns a Maxima string for ‘'dot’ / ‘'mermaid’, or the raw edge
     list ‘[[from, to, weight], ...]’ for ‘'edges’.


